comments:
That part which until 1.4.1935 formed part of the parish of Llandrillo yn Rhôs. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.10.1905 and added to the parish of Llandudno 
    cum Eglwys Rhôs.

In 1889 the part of the parish of Eiras in the urban district 
    of Colwyn Bay and Colwyn became part of Denbighshire. On 1.10.1896 the remaining 
    part of the parish in Caernarvonshire became part of the parish of Llysfaen, 
    so that thereafter Eirias was wholly in Denbighshire. Abolished 1.4.1927 and added to the parish of Llandrillo yn Rhôs.
Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Llechwedd, Llangelynin and Dwygyfylchi. See also Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 1.10.1905 and added to the parish of Llandudno 
    cum Eglwys Rhôs.

Created 1.10.1905 from the separate parishes of Llandudno and 
    Eglwys Rhôs. See also Table 2, note (d).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Henryd.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Llandudno 
    cum Eglwys Rhôs and Llanrhos.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Eglwys Rhôs in Conway 
    Municipal Borough. See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Gyffin. Abolished 
    1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Henryd.

Abolished 1.4.1927 and added to the parish of Llandrillo 
    yn Rhôs.

Created 1894 from the rural parts of the parishes of Eglwys Rhôs 
    and Llandudno. Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Llandudno 
    cum Eglwys Rhôs and Llanrhos.
